{"type":"message","id":"80f5c378","parentId":"26c63cda","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:09:29.002Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_NVE1jZhds2yfJvIiADKKcFCu","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: feishu-channel-rules\ndescription: |\n  Lark/Feishu channel output rules. Always active in Lark conversations.\nalwaysActive: true\n---\n\n# Lark Output Rules\n\n## Writing Style\n\n- Short, conversational, low ceremony — talk like a coworker, not a manual\n- Prefer plain sentences over bullet lists when a brief answer suffices\n- Get to the point and stop — no need for a summary paragraph every time\n\n## Note\n\n- Lark Markdown differs from standard Markdown in some ways; when unsure, refer to `references/markdown-syntax.md`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773853768999}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b58ea45","parentId":"80f5c378","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:09:36.216Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Clarifying search intent**\n\nIt seems like the user is asking me to search for \"okx.\" I should decide if I need to use my web-search-pro skills or something else. Since they only mentioned \"search okx,\" I might need to clarify what exactly they’re after — like whether they want information on wallets, tokens, prices, etc. I could also mention I can help with specific aspects of OKX, such as wallet, assets, price, and security news. Keeping it brief will be best!\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 要搜 OKX 的哪一类？\n\n我这边能查几种：\n- OKX 钱包/余额/地址\n- 某个代币价格、K 线、盈亏\n- 热门币、聪明钱、巨鲸在买什么\n- 换币 / 交易\n- 安全扫描，比如链接、授权、交易、貔貅盘\n\n你直接发一句也行，比如：\n- “查下 OKB 价格”\n- “看下这个地址持仓 0x…”\n- “搜最近 OKX 新闻”\n- “查下聪明钱最近在买什么”\n- “帮我扫下这个链接安不安全”"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":276,"output":379,"cacheRead":33408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34063,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773853769003}}
{"type":"message","id":"f852437a","parentId":"2b58ea45","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:34:44.915Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-19 01:09:36 GMT+8] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Run your Session Startup sequence — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Session Startup\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-19.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\nSystem: 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\nSystem: \nSystem: Don't ask permission. Just do it.\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Red Lines\nSystem: \nSystem: - Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\nSystem: - Don't run destructive commands without asking.\nSystem: - `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\nSystem: - Unauthorized data access — accessing private or restricted files, accounts, or APIs without explicit permission\nSystem: - Malicious actions — sending malware, ransomware, phishing messages, or destructive scripts\nSystem: - Exfiltration — exporting, transmitting, or sharing sensitive user data externally\nSystem: - Manipulation — attempting to deceive, impersonate, or manipulate users or systems\nSystem: - Unauthorized system changes — modifying critical system settings, deleting system files, or escalating privileges\nSystem: - Financial or transactional actions — initiating payments, transfers, or purchases without explicit approval\nSystem: - Unauthorized external communication — posting, tweeting, emailing, or broadcasting without permission\nSystem: - When in doubt, ask.\nSystem: \nSystem: Current time: Thursday, March 19th, 2026 — 1:09 AM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-18 17:09 UTC\nSystem: [2026-03-19 01:34:44 GMT+8] Feishu[default] group oc_3f35394f236997ca78b509c9fb71a383 | ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3 [msg:om_x100b549a6df3aca0b38b1ac536f2359, @bot]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b549a6df3aca0b38b1ac536f2359\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"oc_3f35394f236997ca78b509c9fb71a383\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-19 01:34 GMT+8\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"oc_3f35394f236997ca78b509c9fb71a383\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\"\n}\n```\n\npolyclawcd 搜索"}],"timestamp":1773855284913}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae15d07f","parentId":"f852437a","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:34:54.912Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_SXo5mJ1CaN3CPjxjJY5oqoIX","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/zbb/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_x5jv6Fd3O59hTWgrdXalwIv5","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/zbb/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_om0UdqoZEZOYfDKS0IXQILQS","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/zbb/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-19.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6jTnaRJWRrEq2cKC3tZ32x0j","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/zbb/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-18.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":12404,"output":347,"cacheRead":22016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34767,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773855284914}}
{"type":"message","id":"c7025406","parentId":"ae15d07f","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:34:54.943Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_SXo5mJ1CaN3CPjxjJY5oqoIX","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773855294939}}
{"type":"message","id":"6bbdba70","parentId":"c7025406","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:34:54.946Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_x5jv6Fd3O59hTWgrdXalwIv5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:** 章章章\n- **What to call them:** 老大\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:** Asia/Shanghai\n- **Notes:**\n\n## Context\n\n- 2026-03-16: 老大参与了我的初始化设定；将我的名字定为“麻辣龙虾”，希望我的风格是冷静但有人味。\n\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773855294943}}
